# Security Rules

## Input Validation Security
- Always validate input data before processing
- Use parameterized queries for database operations
- Implement proper CORS configuration
- Validate JWT tokens on protected routes
- Sanitize file uploads

## File Upload Security
```kotlin
// Validate file types
if (originalFileName != null && originalFileName.substringAfterLast(".", "")
        .lowercase() in setOf("jpg", "jpeg", "png", "gif")) {
    // Process file
} else {
    call.respond(
        HttpStatusCode.BadRequest,
        BasicApiResponse<Unit>(
            success = false,
            message = "Invalid image file type"
        )
    )
}
```

## Data Protection
- No hardcoded secrets or credentials
- Use environment variables for sensitive configuration
- No sensitive data in logs
- PII (Personally Identifiable Information) must be protected
- Medical information must be handled securely

## Authentication Security
- JWT tokens must be properly signed and validated
- Token expiration must be appropriately configured
- Refresh token mechanism must be secure
- No sensitive data in JWT payload
- Proper logout functionality implemented

## Authorization Security
- All protected endpoints must require authentication
- Role-based access control must be properly implemented
- Authorization checks must be performed on every request
- No privilege escalation vulnerabilities
- Proper use of route interceptors

## Key Files
- [Security.kt](mdc:src/main/kotlin/Security.kt) - Security configuration
- [AuthInterceptor.kt](mdc:src/main/kotlin/auth/AuthInterceptor.kt) - Authentication logic
- [application.yaml](mdc:src/main/resources/application.yaml) - Configuration